 main lemmas about conditional independence:\n\n```tactics\nnamespace ProbabilityTheory\n\nsection IndepFun\n\nlemma Kernel.IndepFun.of_prod_right {ε Ω : Type*} {mΩ : MeasurableSpace Ω} {mε : MeasurableSpace ε}\n    {μ : Measure Ω} {κ : Kernel Ω α} {X : α → β} {Y : α → γ} {T : α → ε}\n    (h : IndepFun X (fun ω ↦ (Y ω, T ω)) κ μ) :\n    IndepFun X Y κ μ := by\n  rw [Kernel.indepFun_iff_measure_inter_preimage_eq_mul] at h ⊢\n  intro s t hs ht\n  specialize h s (t ×ˢ .univ) hs (ht.prod .univ)\n  simpa [Set.mk_preimage_prod] using h\n\nlemma Kernel.IndepFun.of_prod_left {ε : Type*} {mε : MeasurableSpace ε}\n    [StandardBorelSpace α] [IsFiniteMeasure μ]\n    {X : α → β} {Y : α → γ} {Z : α → δ} {T : α → ε} (h : IndepFun (fun ω ↦ (X ω, T ω)) Y κ μ) :\n    IndepFun X Y κ μ := h.symm.of_prod_right.symm\n```\n\nThese lemmas establish relationships between different forms of independence. The `of_prod_right` lemma shows that if `X` is independent of `Y` given `Z` (in the kernel sense), then `X` is independent of `Y` in the conditional independence sense. The `of_prod_left` lemma shows the symmetric relationship.\n\nNow, we come to the lemma that needs proof:\n\n```tactics\nlemma CondIndepFun.prod_right [StandardBorelSpace α] [StandardBorelSpace β] [Nonempty β]\n    [StandardBorelSpace γ] [Nonempty γ] [StandardBorelSpace δ] [Nonempty δ] [IsFiniteMeasure μ]\n    {X : α → β} {Y : α → γ} {Z : α → δ}\n    (hX : Measurable X) (hY : Measurable Y) (hZ : Measurable Z)\n    (h : X ⟂ᵢ[Z, hZ; μ] Y) :\n    X ⟂ᵢ[Z, hZ; μ] (fun ω ↦ (Y ω, Z ω)) := by\n```\n\nWe need to show that `X` is conditionally independent of `(Y, Z)` given `Z`. The hypothesis is that `X` is conditionally independent of `Y` given `Z`.\n\nTo prove this, we need to show that for any measurable sets `A, B` with `A` measurable with respect to `hZ`, `μ(X⁻¹' A ∩ Z⁻¹' B) = μ((Y, Z)⁻¹' B ∩ Z⁻¹' B)`. \n\nNotice that `(Y, Z)⁻¹' B = Y⁻¹' (B.1) ∩ Z⁻¹' (B.2)`. So, we need to show `μ(X⁻¹' A ∩ Z⁻¹' B) = μ((Y⁻¹' (B.1) ∩ Z⁻¹' (B.2)) ∩ 