  -- Then μ(X⁻¹(s) ∩ Z⁻¹¹(t)) = μ(X⁻¹(s)) * μ(Z⁻¹¹(t)).
  -- This is exactly what the hypothesis gives us, since Z⁻¹¹(t) is just a set in the original space.
  -- So we can directly apply the hypothesis.
  apply h.of_prod_right
